{"word":"ἐμφαίνω","slug":"ἐμφαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐμφαίνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-φᾰνῶ</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐν'><el>ἐν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to let</i> a thing <i>be seen in</i> a mirror, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:— <i>to exhibit, display</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <i>to be seen in</i> a mirror, <i>to be reflected</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to become visible</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}